  <RulesElement name="Horse in a Bottle (heroic tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_15" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 11:33 PM">
    <Flavor> This bottle is filled with a swirling white mist. At times the wisps form the image of a horse head. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 4 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 840 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property"> Uncorking this bottle will cause the mists to bellow out, forming into a white riding horse. Touching the cork to the horse will cause it to reverse this process. If the horse is damaged its hit points will be restored once it's back in the bottle. If its hit points are reduced to zero or less the horse and bottle are destroyed. </specific>
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Encounter * Force): Free Action. Use this ability after successfully dealing damage to a creature in melee combat. You deal an additional 1d4 force damage and the creature is pushed 1 square. </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
