  <RulesElement name="Storyteller's Pipe (heroic tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_31" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 12:27 AM">
    <Flavor> This pipe assists you when regaling an audience with tales of adventure by creating the accompanying images. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 7 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 2600 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property"> When smoking this pipe the owner can choose to shape the smoke it emits into various images. It's often used by sages, storytellers, and entertainers to enhance or support whatever message they're trying to convey. In rare cases it can be used to assist in communication with creatures that don't speak the same language. An innovative player may find a number of unique uses for this. As a basic benefit however the owner gains a +2 bonus to bluff and diplomacy skill checks in situations where they can utilize the pipe. </specific>
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Encounter): Free Action. Your square and the squares adjacent to you are considered lightly obscured until the end of your next turn. Sustain minor; you may not move more than 2 squares while sustaining the effect. </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Sweetstone (heroic tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_32" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 12:38 AM">
    <Flavor> A favorite at outdoor events, this stone attracts bugs to it, allowing the festivities to proceed pest free. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 2 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 520 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property"> Dropping this fist sized stone into a square will cause it to attract all non-monstrous bugs (normal ants, gnats, mosquitoes, flies, etc.) within 30 squares to it. </specific>
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Daily): Minor Action. Drop the stone into an adjacent square and spend a healing surge. If you do, you do not regain hit points as normal. Instead make an attack against up to 3 natural beast creatures within 5 squares of the stone: +5 vs. Will; hit: creatures shift to the closest unoccupied square adjacent to the stone and become stunned (save ends). </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Traveler's Bed (heroic tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_33" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 12:42 AM">
    <Flavor> A tiny carved model of a four poster bed, complete with tiny covers and pillows. It becomes full size on command. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 2 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 520 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property"> Placing this item in an unoccupied square and speaking a command phrase will cause this coin size bed to expand into a queen size bed. The bed must have sufficient room for this expansion or else it will not function. A second command phrase will cause it to shrink. You gain 1d8 temporary hit points after an extended rest in this bed. You lose any temporary hit points you may have remaining the next time the bed is used. </specific>
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power" />
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Universal Uniform (heroic tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_34" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 12:45 AM">
    <Flavor> When wrapped around you this cloak can mimic the required apparel of any group you decide to infiltrate. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 7 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 2600 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property" />
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Daily): Minor Action. When you trigger this ability the cloak briefly creates a 40 x 40 square zone. It scans what is being worn by humanoid creatures within this area and then transforms into a duplicate of whatever its found the most of. For instance: in a castle, it might duplicate the armor of the palace guard, in an evil temple if might duplicate a cultist's robes. This transformation is only on the surface and does not affect the AC of whatever else you're wearing. While in 'uniform' you gain a +2 bonus to Bluff and Diplomacy checks made versus others in the same 'uniform'. This transformation lasts for up to 3 hours or until the wearer wills it to cease. </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Wizard's Chessboard (paragon tier)" type="Magic Item" internal-id="ID_EOF_MAGIC_ITEM_11005_35" source="Buck-A-Batch Wondrous Items 2" revision-date="6/26/2011 12:51 AM">
    <Flavor> This magic chess board provides an opponent for gaming and an ally in battle. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Level"> 13 </specific>
    <specific name="Gold"> 17000 </specific>
    <specific name="Magic Item Type"> Wondrous Item </specific>
    <specific name="Tier" />
    <specific name="_Item_Set_ID" />
    <specific name="Armor" />
    <specific name="Weapon" />
    <specific name="Item Slot" />
    <specific name="Requirement" />
    <specific name="Critical" />
    <specific name="Property"> Setting this board on a level surface and placing the chess pieces in their proper position will begin a game of chess. The game board magically moves the pieces providing a challenging game adjusted to the player's skill. </specific>
    <specific name="Special" />
    <specific name="Power"> Power (Daily * Conjuration): Standard Action. By tossing a pawn into an unoccupied square adjacent to you, you summon a medium sized metal fighter, either completely white or completely black depending upon the piece tossed. The fighter shares your defenses with a +1 bonus to AC. It has hit points equal to 2x your healing surge value and resist 5 radiant if white, resist 5 necrotic if black. The fighter is treated as one of your allies, can flank enemies, and deals 10 damage to an enemy adjacent to it that is hit by an ally's attack. As a move action, you can cause the fighter to shift 1 square or move 4 squares. The fighter disappears when reduced to 0 hit points, or the encounter ends, the soldier disappears leaving the chess piece behind. </specific>
    <specific name="_Rarity"> Common </specific>
    <specific name="Granted Powers" />
  </RulesElement>
